    "media:imagetext": "STATE OF CALIFORNIA\nDEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC WORKS\nDIVISION OF HIGHWAYS\nPUBICWORKS EULONG\nELEVENTH AND P STREETS\nSACRAMENTO, CALIFORNIA\nAOORESS ALL COMMUNICATIONS\nOctober 8th, 1929.\nIN YOUR REPLY PLEASE\nREFER TO FILE No..\nMr.,\nRight of Way Department,\nCity of San Francisco,\nSan Francisco, California.\nDear Sir:\nThis will acknowledge receipt of your letter of\nOctober 1st to Mr. C. H. Purcell requesting information as to\nthe attitude of this Department in the matter of railroad cross-\nings on the Bay Shore Highway.\nMr. Purcell is out of town at the present time\nbut upon his return your letter will be called to his attention.\nYours\nG.\nCOOK\nSecy\n*to Stảte Highway Engineer.",
